C%22https%3A%2F%2Fselectcommitteeontheccp.house.gov%2Fsites%2Fevo-subsites%2Fselectcommitteeontheccp.house.gov%2Ffiles%2Fevo-media-document%2FProtecting%2520Americans%2520From%2520Foriegn%2520Adversary%2520Controlled%2520Applications_3.5.24.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebill%3C%2Fa%3E%20dubbed%20the%20Protecting%20Americans%20from%20Foreign%20Adversary%20Controlled%20Applications%20Act%2C%20would%20force%20TikTok's%20Beijing-based%20parent%20company%2C%20ByteDance%2C%20to%20sell%20its%20US%20operations%20of%20the%20video-sharing%20platform%20to%20a%20non-Chinese%20company%20within%20six%20months%20or%20have%20to%20grapple%20with%20a%20nationwide%20ban%20on%20the%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%2C%20which%20a%20House%20of%20Representatives%20committee%20unanimously%20green-lighted%20in%20a%2050-0%20vote%20last%20week%2C%20says%20it%20seeks%20to%20%26quot%3Bprotect%20the%20national%20security%20of%20the%20United%20States%20from%20the%20threat%20posed%20by%20foreign%20adversary%20controlled%20applications%2C%20such%20as%20TikTok%20and%20any%20successor%20application%20or%20service%20and%20any%20other%20application%20or%20service%20developed%20or%20provided%20by%20ByteDance%20Ltd.%20or%20an%20entity%20under%20the%20control%20of%20ByteDance%20Ltd.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Republican-controlled%20House%20is%20expected%20to%20vote%20on%20the%20bill%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20must%20ensure%20the%20Chinese%20government%20cannot%20weaponize%20TikTok%20against%20American%20users%20and%20our%20government%20through%20data%20collection%20and%20propaganda%2C%26quot%3B%20GOP%20Rep.%20Steve%20Scalise%2C%20the%20House%20majority%20leader%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftiktok-us-security-threat-says-trump-similar-facebook-cnbc-2024-03-11%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublican%20Rep.%20Cathy%20McMorris%20Rodgers%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20House%20Energy%20and%20Commerce%20Committee%2C%20which%20voted%20to%20approve%20the%20bill%2C%20said%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dp2IAUHBsPZI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Fox%20Business%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20real%20national%20security%20threat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bill%20is%20narrow%2C%26quot%3B%20McMorris%20Rodgers%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20targeted%20to%20address%20the%20national%20security%20threat%20that%20we%20believe%20these%20apps%2C%20like%20TikTok%2C%20pose%20to%20the%20United%20States%20because%20of%20its%20ownership%20by%20a%20foreign%20adversary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKreps%20told%20BI%20that%20she%20was%20more%20confident%20this%20bill%20would%20go%20further%20than%20past%20attempts%20to%20ban%20TikTok%20in%20the%20US%20because%20the%20cosponsors%20of%20the%20bill%20appeared%20to%20have%20done%20%26quot%3Bthe%20legal%20legwork%20to%20identify%20the%20weaknesses%20of%20previous%20versions%20and%20address%20those%20concerns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20bill%2C%20if%20passed%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20face%20legal%20challenges%20by%20ByteDance%20and%20TikTok%20on%20First%20Amendment%20grounds%2C%20according%20to%20Kreps%20and%20other%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECiting%20national%20security%20is%20'not%20a%20get%20out%20of%20jail%20free%20card'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERamya%20Krishnan%2C%20a%20staff%20attorney%20at%20the%20Knight%20First%20Amendment%20Institute%20at%20Columbia%20University%20in%20New%20York%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20very%20clear%20that%20invoking%20national%20security%20is%20not%20a%20'get%20out%20of%20jail%20free'%20card%20for%20having%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20First%20Amendment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20First%20Amendment%20protects%20Americans'%20right%20to%20access%20social%20media%20platforms%20of%20their%20choosing%2C%26quot%3B%20Krishnan%20said.%20%26quot%3BTo%20justify%20a%20ban%2C%20the%20government%20would%20have%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20the%20privacy%20and%20security%20concerns%20it%20has%20can't%20be%20addressed%20in%20narrower%20ways.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20government%20simply%20hasn't%20done%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Krishnan%2C%20who%20called%20the%20bill%20%26quot%3Bunconstitutional%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20that%20a%20ban%20on%20TikTok%20%26quot%3Bwould%20set%20a%20dangerous%20precedent%20for%20how%20we%20regulate%20free%20speech%20online.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20there's%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnetworkcontagion.us%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2FA-Tik-Tok-ing-Timebomb_12.21.23.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20suggest%20that%20TikTok%20suppresses%20content%20around%20political%20speech%2C%20the%20US%20government%20%26quot%3Bhasn't%20pointed%20to%20any%20evidence%20that%20China%20uses%20TikTok's%20algorithm%20to%20promote%20disinformation%2C%26quot%3B%20Krishnan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20fundamentally%2C%26quot%3B%20Krishnan%2C%20a%20lecturer%20at%20Columbia%20Law%20School%2C%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20First%20Amendment%20doesn't%20permit%20the%20government%20to%20suppress%20media%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20it%20contains%20disinformation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommunist-party-god-credential-data-bytedance-tiktok-former-executive-alleges-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erepeatedly%20denied%20allegations%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20has%20ties%20to%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20and%20has%20been%20fighting%20back%20against%20the%20new%20bill%20that%20could%20see%20the%20social%20media%20app%20banned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20last%20week%2C%20TikTok%20said%20the%20US%20government%20was%20%26quot%3Battempting%20to%20strip%20170%20million%20Americans%20of%20their%20Constitutional%20right%20to%20free%20expression.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20will%20damage%20millions%20of%20businesses%2C%20deny%20artists%20an%20audience%2C%20and%20destroy%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20countless%20creators%20across%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224786%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trump%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e62946ce7f1785b2e618c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223191%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20Tulsa%2C%20Okla.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FSue%20Ogrocki%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ETrump%20once%20supported%20a%20TikTok%20ban%2C%20but%20is%20now%20against%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Trump%20%E2%80%94%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tiktok-ban-sold-by-sept-15-microsoft-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadministration%20tried%20to%20ban%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20but%20was%20blocked%20from%20doing%20so%20in%20court%20after%20TikTok%20sued%20%E2%80%94%20has%20now%20come%20out%20against%20a%20ban%20for%20the%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20get%20rid%20of%20TikTok%2C%20Facebook%20and%20Zuckerschmuck%20will%20double%20their%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20argued%20on%20his%20social%20media%20platform%2C%20Truth%20Social%2C%20in%20a%20dig%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fmark-zuckerberg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20CEO%20and%20Facebook%20founder%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20House%20Energy%20and%20Commerce%20Committee%20unanimously%20voted%20to%20advance%20the%20bill%2C%20several%20groups%2C%20including%20the%20American%20Civil%20Liberties%20Union%20and%20the%20Center%20for%20Democracy%20and%20Technology%2C%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20committee%20urging%20members%20to%20oppose%20the%20bill%20that%20they%20called%20%26quot%3Bcensorship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20deeply%20disappointed%20that%20the%20committee%20chose%20to%20ignore%20the%20serious%20First%20Amendment%20concerns%20raised%20by%20civil%20liberties%20groups%20and%20instead%20voted%20to%20advance%20this%20bill%20that%20would%20silence%20over%20170%20million%20people%20around%20the%20country%20who%20use%20TikTok%20every%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Jenna%20Leventoff%2C%20senior%20policy%20counsel%20at%20ACLU%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20after%20the%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20this%20bill%20comes%20to%20the%20floor%20for%20a%20vote%2C%20we%20urge%20representatives%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20free%20speech%2C%20and%20vote%20down%20this%20misguided%20bill%2C%26quot%3B%20Leventoff%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-bill-national-security-threat-framing-congress-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710273535000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c3f02743bb77284ba4ad34%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-bill-national-security-threat-framing-congress-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bipartisan%20bill%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20the%20banning%20of%20TikTok%20in%20the%20US%20could%20be%20bolstered%20by%20its%20framing%20around%20a%20threat%20to%20national%20security.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nmusumeci%40businessinsider.com%20(Natalie%20Musumeci)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-bill-national-security-threat-framing-congress-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20went%20to%20SXSW%20and%20saw%20Netflix%20and%20Amazon%20competing%20with%20splashy%20sci-fi%2C%20while%20Paramount%2B%20pitched%20its%20whole%20line-up%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22