sed%20since%20April%2012%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20data%20was%20to%20include%20the%20date%20the%20bonds%20were%20purchased%20on%2C%20their%20denominations%20and%20the%20names%20of%20who%20purchased%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20said%20ordered%20for%20data%20on%20every%20electoral%20bond%20encashed%20by%20political%20parties%20since%20that%20date%20to%20be%20furnished%2C%20including%20the%20date%20they%20were%20encashed%20on%20and%20the%20bonds%E2%80%99%20denominations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20before%20the%20March%206%20deadline%2C%20the%20SBI%20said%20it%20needed%20time%20till%20June%2030%20to%20furnish%20the%20data%20because%20it%20had%20to%20compile%2044%2C434%20sets%20of%20information%20from%20two%20%E2%80%98information%20silos%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20asked%20the%20bank%20what%20it%20had%20done%20since%20February%2015%20and%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20bank%20already%20had%20the%20necessary%20information%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theweek.in%2Fnews%2Fbiz-tech%2F2024%2F02%2F05%2Fsbi-issues-electoral-bonds-worth-rs-16518-crore-in-30-tranches.html%5C%22%3ERs%2016%2C518%20crore%20worth%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20sold%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%202018%20to%20the%20start%20of%202024%2C%20the%20government%20recently%20informed%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20BJP%20has%20by%20far%20been%20the%20biggest%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20number%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20%E2%80%93%20worth%20Rs%2012%2C008%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20sold%20between%202017-2018%20and%202022-2023%2C%20the%20BJP%20received%20nearly%2055%25%2C%20or%20Rs%206%2C564%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20a%20developing%20story%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710250529000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04200200%2F3076973126_ab45efee1b_k.jpg%22%2