3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3Ebolts%20of%20the%20foreigners%2C%20and%20on%20the%20other%2C%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3Ethunderbolts%20of%20Mother%20Nature.%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20location%20might%20hold%20more%20meanings%20than%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20semi-humorous%20statement%20betrays.%20From%20the%20open%20spaces%20of%20the%20ashram%20on%20the%20western%20bank%20of%20the%20Sabarmati%2C%20from%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20house%2C%20or%20from%20the%20prayer%20ground%2C%20the%20dwellers%20at%20the%20ashram%20could%20see%20a%20distinct%20panorama.%20On%20the%20opposite%20bank%20of%20the%20river%2C%20clearly%20and%20continuously%20visible%2C%20stood%20the%20skyline%20of%20the%20city%2C%20marked%20by%20the%20many%20chimneys%20of%20textile%20mills.%20The%20walls%20of%20the%20historical%20city%20and%20the%20suburb%20of%20Shahibag%20were%20also%20visible%2C%20as%20was%20the%20south-western%20edge%20of%20the%20British%20army%20cantonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPositioning%20the%20ashram%20at%20this%20location%20shows%20to%20the%20ashram%20resident%20the%20ways%20of%20life%20and%20the%20structures%20of%20society%20and%20economy%20which%20the%20colonial%20settlement%2C%20the%20industrial%20city%20as%20well%20as%20the%20tradition-bound%20walled%20city%20demonstrate.%20To%20city%20dwellers%2C%20the%20ashram%20demonstrates%20an%20entirely%20different%20idea%20of%20how%20life%20might%20be%20lived.%20It%20offers%20to%20the%20dweller%20of%20the%20traditional%20city%2C%20the%20worker%20and%20owner%20of%20industry%20as%20much%20as%20the%20colonialist%20not%20only%20an%20alternate%20model%20but%20it%20presents%20a%20challenge%20to%20them%20as%20well.%20The%20view%20from%20the%20ashram%20was%20a%20constant%20question%20to%20the%20ashramites%2C%20just%20as%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20ashram%20presented%20questions%20to%20the%20city%20dwellers%2C%20both%20native%20and%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F12161230%2Fimage-1940.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221077%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F12161230%2Fimage-1940.png%201077w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F12161230%2Fimage-1940-300x147.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F12161230%2Fimage-1940-1024x500.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-701284%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22526%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHome%20for%20a%20Mendicant%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Tridip%20Suhrud%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Phoenix%20Settlement%20and%20the%20Tolstoy%20Farm%20in%20South%20Africa%20had%20%E2%80%98ashramic%20character%E2%80%99%20especially%20after%20the%20advent%20of%20Satyagraha%20in%201906.%20The%20community%20at%20Sabarmati%20was%20ashramic%2C%20in%20the%20full%20sense.%20That%20is%2C%20each%20member%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20Ashram%20observances%20and%20the%20ideal%20conduct%20that%20they%20were%20expected%20to%20strive%20towards%2C%20if%20not%20attain%20in%20every%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ashram%20and%20its%20community%20were%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20experiment%20and%20the%20site%20for%20his%20experiments.%20It%20was%20a%20community%20that%20had%20its%20foundations%20in%20Truth.%20It%20was%20the%20Satyagraha%20Ashram.%20In%20absence%20of%20truth%2C%20or%20even%20in%20case%20of%20violation%20of%20it%2C%20the%20Ashram%20could%20not%20be.%20It%20was%20simultaneously%20a%20community%20that%20aspired%20to%20%3Ci%3Eahimsa%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20not%20only%20as%20a%20negation%2C%20as%20non-violence%20but%20as%20active%20working%20of%20love.%20This%20community%20sought%20to%20lead%20a%20life%20of%20non-stealing%2C%20which%20included%20in%20its%20understanding%20%E2%80%98Bread-Labour%E2%80%99%20and%20non-acquisition.%20This%20community%20sought%20to%20cultivate%20equability%20or%20%3Ci%3Esamabhava%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20about%20religion%20and%20on%20the%20practice%20of%20untouchability.%20%3Ci%3Esamabhava%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3EGandhi%20knew%2C%20is%20possible%20only%20when%20the%20sense%20of%20%3Ci%3Emamabhava%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20of%20%E2%80%98mine-ness%E2%80%99%2C%20of%20possession%20disappears.%20Gandhi%20had%20hoped%20that%20his%20Ashram%20would%20be%20like%20the%20%3Ci%3Esthitprajna%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20a%20person%20whose%20intellect%20is%20secure%20as%20described%20in%20the%20Bhagvad%20Gita%3Ci%3E.%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98When%20it%20is%20night%20for%20all%20other%20beings%2C%20the%20disciplined%20soul%20is%20awake!%20When%20all%20other%20beings%20are%20awake%20it%20is%20the%20night%20for%20the%20seeing%20ascetic.%E2%80%991%20Such%20an%20Ashram%20Gandhi%20believed%20was%20his%20only%20creation%2C%20the%20only%20measure%20by%20which%20he%20would%20be%20judged%20and%20would%20like%20to%20be%20judged.%20He%20said%20of%20the%20Ashram%20in%201925%2C%20%E2%80%98It%20is%20my%20best%20and%20only%20creation.%20The%20world%20will%20judge%20me%20by%20its%20results.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGandhi%20had%20one%20deeply%20felt%20need%2C%20desire%2C%20want%20and%20aspiration%3B%20to%20be%20an%20ashramite%20in%20the%20sense%20of%20living%20for%20a%20length%20of%20time%20in%20the%20communities%20that%20he%20had%20created.%20His%20oft%20repeated%20lament%20was%20that%20his%20work%20and%20obligation%20to%20myriad%20causes%20made%20him%20an%20itinerant%20ashramite.%20The%20ashram%20observances%20went%20with%20him%2C%20but%20the%20community%20of%20co-religionists%20could%20not.%20This%20was%20true%20not%20only%20of%20ashram%20at%20Sabarmati%2C%20but%20also%20of%20the%20Phoenix%20Settlement%20and%20the%20Tolstoy%20Farm.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710243018000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F1